ies for each one<\/li>\n<li>Creative ideas, actionable tips, and unobvious intel to help inform your strategy<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Let\u2019s dive in.<\/p>\n<h3>Contents<\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#the-most-popular-social-media-platforms\">The most popular social media platforms in 2025<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#the-most-popular-social-media-platforms-in-us\">The most popular social media platforms in the US in 2025<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#the-most-popular-social-media-platforms-for-marketers\">The most popular social media platforms for marketers in 2025<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#facebook-facts\">Facebook facts<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#instagram-intel\">Instagram intel<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#twitter-tidbits\">X (Twitter) tidbits<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#linkedin-low-down\">LinkedIn low-down<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#tiktok-tidings\">TikTok tidings<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#snapchat-savvy\">Snapchat savvy<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div id=\"the-most-popular-social-media-platforms\"><\/div>\n<h2>The most popular social media platforms in 2025<\/h2>\n<p>We compared <a href=\"https:\/\/www.statista.com\/statistics\/272014\/global-social-networks-ranked-by-number-of-users\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Statista\u2019s data<\/a> as of July 2023 to the same chart from last year. These are the most popular social media platforms worldwide and how they\u2019ve moved on the list since a year ago.<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Facebook<\/li>\n<li>YouTube<\/li>\n<li>WhatsApp<\/li>\n<li>Instagram<\/li>\n<li>WeChat<\/li>\n<li>TikTok<\/li>\n<li>[\ud83d\udd3b2] Facebook Messenger<\/li>\n<li>[\ud83d\udd3a1] Telegram<\/li>\n<li>[\ud83d\udd3a2] Snapchat<\/li>\n<li>[\ud83d\udd3b2] Douyin<\/li>\n<li>[\ud83d\udd3a1] Kuaishou<\/li>\n<li>[\ud83d\udd3a3] X (Twitter)<\/li>\n<li>[\ud83d\udd3b3] Sina Weibo<\/li>\n<li>[\ud83d\udd3b7] QQ<\/li>\n<li>[\ud83d\udd3b2] Pinterest<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-marketers-11.jpg\" alt=\"Most popular social media platforms - bar graph of most popular social apps\" width=\"936\" height=\"600\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-76885 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-marketers-11.jpg 936w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-marketers-11-480x308.jpg 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>The top four most popular social media platforms in the world are Facebook, YouTube, WhatsApp, and Instagram. TikTok comes in at six, but X (formerly known as Twitter) is number 15 and LinkedIn isn\u2019t even on there.<\/p>\n<p>This may seem surprising, but while <a href=\"https:\/\/nobelbiz.com\/report-social-media-customer-support\/#:~:text=More%20and%20more%20customers%20now,support%20requests%20over%20social%20channels.\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">80%<\/a> of customers engage with brands on social media, not all social media platforms are designed for this use case. Some are purely for instant messaging and some platforms are wildly popular in other areas of the world, like China.<\/p>\n<p>Let\u2019s narrow our list down to the most popular social media platforms in the US.<\/p>\n<div id=\"the-most-popular-social-media-platforms-in-us\"><\/div>\n<h2>The most popular social media platforms in the US in 2025<\/h2>\n<p>Raw monthly average user data specific to US users for social platforms isn\u2019t easily available. So we\u2019ve leaned on a recent survey from <a href=\"https:\/\/blog.hubspot.com\/marketing\/fastest-growing-social-media-platforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">HubSpot<\/a> to give us a clue as to which social networks are getting the lion\u2019s share of attention.<\/p>\n<p>Here are the 12 most popular social media platforms in the US, according to that survey:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Facebook<\/li>\n<li>YouTube<\/li>\n<li>Instagram<\/li>\n<li>TikTok<\/li>\n<li>X<\/li>\n<li>Pinterest<\/li>\n<li>Snapchat<\/li>\n<li>Reddit<\/li>\n<li>LinkedIn<\/li>\n<li>Twitch<\/li>\n<li>Tumblr<\/li>\n<li>BeReal<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-US.jpg\" alt=\"Most popular social media platforms - copy of HubSpot graph\" width=\"936\" height=\"541\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-76864 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-US.jpg 936w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-US-480x277.jpg 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><a href=\"https:\/\/blog.hubspot.com\/marketing\/fastest-growing-social-media-platforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source<\/a><\/em><\/p>\n<p>The data isn\u2019t ideal since it\u2019s a self-reported survey versus hard numbers from the apps themselves. But it does give us an answer to another interesting question: <strong>What\u2019s the fastest-growing social media platform?<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>In percentage of reported users year-over-year, upstart platform BeReal saw a huge 313% increase. No surprise that <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2023\/08\/23\/tiktok-marketing\">TikTok<\/a> had the biggest gain among more established social media apps. And since nine out of the 12 platforms listed got a bump, it seems that overall social media usage is growing.<\/p>\n<p>One unexpected turn is that <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/07\/29\/promote-your-business-on-youtube\">YouTube<\/a> lost ground compared to last year. It\u2019ll be interesting to see if that continues as <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/how-to-promote-your-youtube-channel-for-free\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">YouTube Shorts<\/a> gain acceptance.<\/p>\n<p>\ud83d\uded1 Want to get more clicks and conversions from EVERY digital marketing channel? Download this massive guide of <a href=\"https:\/\/marketing.localiq.com\/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteBestOnlineMarketingTips.html?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_130marketingtips_Download\">130+ of the best online marketing tips<\/a> to learn how.<\/p>\n<div id=\"the-most-popular-social-media-platforms-for-marketers\"><\/div>\n<h2>The most popular social media platforms for marketers in 2025<\/h2>\n<p>According to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.statista.com\/statistics\/259379\/social-media-platforms-used-by-marketers-worldwide\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Statista<\/a>, the most popular social media platforms for marketing are:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Facebook<\/li>\n<li>Instagram<\/li>\n<li>LinkedIn<\/li>\n<li>YouTube<\/li>\n<li>X<\/li>\n<li>TikTok<\/li>\n<li>Snapchat<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-marketers.jpg\" alt=\"Most popular social media platforms - graph showing most popular social media sites for marketers\" width=\"936\" height=\"600\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-76880 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-marketers.jpg 936w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-marketers-480x308.jpg 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>This is based on another self-reported survey. Note that <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2019\/03\/05\/linkedin-advertising\">LinkedIn<\/a> is number three here even though it barely cracked the top 10 by U.S. users. That\u2019s because even with a smaller user base, LinkedIn is built for professional communication so it\u2019s a concentrated pool of prospects for many marketers.<\/p>\n<p>In the rest of this post, we\u2019re going to explore what is popular on each of these platforms and how to incorporate them into your <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/social-media-marketing\">social media marketing strategy<\/a>.<\/p>\n<div id=\"facebook-facts\"><\/div>\n<h2>Facebook is the most popular social media platform for\u2026<\/h2>\n<p>Everything\u2026just kidding (sort of). It is the biggest social media platform worldwide and its versatility makes it a go-to for just about anything. But in particular, Facebook is best for the following:<\/p>\n<h3>Local marketing<\/h3>\n<p>Did you know that Facebook is right up there with Google My Business as one of the <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/best-free-business-listing-sites\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">top local business directories?<\/a> When you think about what a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2017\/10\/16\/facebook-business-page\">Facebook business page<\/a> contains, this shouldn\u2019t come as a surprise. This includes:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Description, category, price range<\/li>\n<li>Contact info, hours, photos<\/li>\n<li>Call to action button, reviews, instant messaging<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-facebook-local-business-directory.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - facebook as a local business directory\" width=\"600\" height=\"401\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54109\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-facebook-local-business-directory.png 600w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-facebook-local-business-directory-480x321.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/business\/pages?content_id=73Fq4YhMRSagPXl&amp;ref=sem_smb&amp;utm_source=GOOGLE&amp;utm_medium=fbsmbsem&amp;utm_campaign=PFX_SEM_G_Pages_CA_EN_Brand_Exact_Desktop&amp;utm_content=Facebook-Marketing_Evaluating&amp;kenid=_k_CjwKCAiAxKv_BRBdEiwAyd40N7oBz-5plU2dLkZUvtXmN1NyE6noL4ZSlDB89DnMI_Iy-4Pccojm8BoCxy0QAvD_BwE_k_&amp;utm_term=marketing%20on%20facebook&amp;utm_ct=EVG&amp;gclid=CjwKCAiAxKv_BRBdEiwAyd40N7oBz-5plU2dLkZUvtXmN1NyE6noL4ZSlDB89DnMI_Iy-4Pccojm8BoCxy0QAvD_BwE\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">60% of Facebook users<\/a> visit a local business Page at least once a week, so promote your page, and use it to build relationships, keep customers updated, and connect with your local community. <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/how-to-promote-your-facebook-page-for-free\/\"><\/a><\/p>\n<p><strong>\ud83c\udfac Action time:<\/strong> Learn how to <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/how-to-promote-your-facebook-page-for-free\/\">promote your Facebook business page for free<\/a> or try these <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2018\/07\/02\/facebook-marketing-for-small-business\">22 budget-friendly Facebook marketing tips.<\/a><\/p>\n<h3>Advertising<\/h3>\n<p>While your business page is a popular hub for those who know about your business, Facebook isn\u2019t the best platform for reaching new audiences organically. In fact, its organic reach is <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ignitesocialmedia.com\/social-media-strategy\/social-media-organic-reach-2021-who-actually-sees-your-content\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">2.2%<\/a> (compared to Instagram at 9.4%).<\/p>\n<p>On the other hand, thanks to its size and targeting capabilities, Facebook is <a href=\"https:\/\/postclick.com\/blog\/best-advertising-platforms\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">tied with Google<\/a> as a top digital advertising platform. Facebook ads can reach up to <a href=\"https:\/\/influencermarketinghub.com\/social-media-marketing-benchmark-report\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">36.7%<\/a> of the adult population, the highest percentage of all social media platforms (X is the lowest, at 6.5%).<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-facebook-ad-example.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - facebook ad example\" width=\"500\" height=\"639\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54127\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-facebook-ad-example.png 500w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-facebook-ad-example-480x613.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 500px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>An average Facebook user clicks on <a href=\"https:\/\/hootsuite.com\/resources\/digital2020-q4-update\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">12 ads per month<\/a> and the volume of impressions can raise brand awareness and improve your ad performance elsewhere. In terms of cost, the average conversion rate and cost per conversion on Facebook is 9.21% and $18.68, compared to 4.40% and $56.11 for Google Search.<\/p>\n<p>Compared to Instagram, Facebook\u2019s cost per click and click-through rate is <a href=\"https:\/\/www.socialinsider.io\/blog\/facebook-ads-vs-instagram-ads\/#cpcvalues\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">$0.49<\/a> and 3.06%, vs Instagram at $1.09 and 0.68%.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-facebook-cpc.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - cpc for facebook vs instagram\" width=\"717\" height=\"442\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54116\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-facebook-cpc.png 717w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-facebook-cpc-480x296.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 717px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>&#8230;to ages 65+<\/h3>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/influencermarketinghub.com\/social-media-marketing-benchmark-report\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Influencer Marketing Hub<\/a> also tells us that age 65+ is the fastest-growing demographic for Facebook ad reach. In 2021, this group grew by 25%. Now this, of course, doesn&#8217;t mean that this is the most popular age group on Facebook. It&#8217;s still 25-34, but for the 65+ age group, it is the preferred platform.<\/p>\n<h3>Links and photos (or maybe not?)<\/h3>\n<p>Here&#8217;s an interesting find. According to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.statista.com\/statistics\/296628\/facebook-brand-post-interaction\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Statista<\/a>, photos and links are the leading types of branded posts on Facebook (videos and status updates pale in comparison). BUT this is just <strong>quantity<\/strong> of posts\u2014not <strong>engagement<\/strong> of posts. So on the one hand, links and photos are a good bet since they&#8217;re what users expect, but they&#8217;re most frequent because they&#8217;re the easiest to create. Which means that posting videos can give you a competitive edge.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-facebook-post-types.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - facebook post types\" width=\"650\" height=\"500\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55304\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-facebook-post-types.png 650w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-facebook-post-types-480x369.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 650px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p><strong>\ud83c\udfac Action time:<\/strong> Get with these <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/03\/10\/facebook-post-ideas\">62 engaging Facebook post ideas<\/a> and check out these <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2020\/07\/28\/facebook-video-marketing\">9 ways to level up your Facebook video marketing<\/a>\u2014which include finding your &#8220;aha&#8221; moment, formatting properly, using captions, and more.<\/p>\n<h3>Community and relationship-building<\/h3>\n<p>Don&#8217;t let Facebook&#8217;s low organic reach deter you from using it to engage with your audience. Many people often use a business&#8217;s Facebook page to check for announcements, store closings, sales, and other recent information. If you use your page in this manner, your customers and close followers will know to check your page frequently and you won&#8217;t have to worry as much about <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/facebook-news-feed\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">showing up in their feeds.<\/a><\/p>\n<p>You can then cater your posts to the quality traffic you are getting to your page\u2014sparking discussions and engaging back with individuals, encouraging direct messaging, and more.<\/p>\n<h3>The most popular industries on Facebook<\/h3>\n<p>Facebook can work for any industry or business, but according to the data, we can see that for ads, the industries that see the highest conversion rates are<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Beauty and fitness<\/li>\n<li>Jobs and education<\/li>\n<li>Employment and job training<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/facebook-ads-conversion-rate-benchmarks.png\" alt=\"facebook ads conversion rate benchmarks\" width=\"793\" height=\"802\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-13381\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/facebook-ads-conversion-rate-benchmarks.png 793w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/facebook-ads-conversion-rate-benchmarks-480x485.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 793px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2019\/11\/12\/facebook-ad-benchmarks\"> View our Facebook advertising benchmarks here.<\/a><\/em><\/p>\n<p>For organic engagement, we see that healthcare, restaurants, and finance verticals see the highest engagement rates.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-facebook-engagement-rate.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - facebook engagement by industry\" width=\"600\" height=\"740\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54137\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-facebook-engagement-rate.png 600w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-facebook-engagement-rate-480x592.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.socialinsider.io\/blog\/social-media-industry-benchmarks\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Image source<\/em><\/a><\/p>\n<p><strong>\ud83c\udfac Action time:<\/strong> Learn how to master the organic Facebook algorithm with these <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/facebook-news-feed\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">6 ways to show up in the Facebook News Feed<\/a>.<br \/>\n<a id=\"instagram\"><\/a><\/p>\n<div id=\"instagram-intel\"><\/div>\n<h2>Instagram is the most popular social media platform for\u2026<\/h2>\n<p>Don\u2019t worry, I\u2019m not going to say visual marketing! Visual marketing should not be an isolated strategy. It should be a staple for all of your strategies, not just on social media. Here is where Instagram stands out above the rest:<\/p>\n<h3>Ecommerce<\/h3>\n<p>Instagram advertising costs may be higher than Facebook, but that doesn\u2019t mean it\u2019s not a good channel for <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/02\/02\/reasons-to-advertise-on-social-media\">paid social advertising<\/a>. First of all, purchase intent is highest on Instagram, with <a href=\"https:\/\/sproutsocial.com\/insights\/instagram-stats\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">36%<\/a> of users using it to follow brands (compared to just 19% for Facebook).<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/use-of-social-media.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"1055\" height=\"600\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-76938\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/use-of-social-media.webp 1055w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/use-of-social-media-980x557.webp 980w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/use-of-social-media-480x273.webp 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1055px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Instagram also has the highest organic engagement rate between users and brands\u2014<a href=\"https:\/\/contrast.digital\/blog\/ecommerce-statistics\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">10<\/a> times greater than Facebook, 54 times greater than Pinterest, and 84 times greater than X. And with shoppable ads, Instagram has turned planned shopping on its head and folded product discovery and impulse buying into our organic behaviors, making it the most influential social media platform on our shopping habits.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-instagram-impact-selling.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - channels with most influence on shopping habits\" width=\"650\" height=\"457\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54125\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-instagram-impact-selling.png 650w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-instagram-impact-selling-480x337.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 650px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.retailtouchpoints.com\/resources\/72-of-users-make-purchase-decisions-based-on-instagram-content\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Image source<\/em><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Still not convinced?<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/passport-photo.online\/blog\/how-people-use-instagram\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">71%<\/a> of Instagram users feel more connected to brands they follow on Instagram<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/blog.hootsuite.com\/instagram-statistics\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">81%<\/a> of people say Instagram helps them to research or discover new products or services.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.retailtouchpoints.com\/resources\/72-of-users-make-purchase-decisions-based-on-instagram-content\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">72%<\/a> report making purchase decisions based on something they saw on Instagram (compared to Facebook at 23%).<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/blog.hootsuite.com\/instagram-statistics\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">130 million<\/a> users tap on shopping posts every month.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/business.instagram.com\/a\/stories\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">50% of people<\/a> have visited a website to make a purchase after seeing a product or service in Stories.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-instagram-shopping-ad.jpeg\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - instagram shopping example\" width=\"720\" height=\"416\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54126\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-instagram-shopping-ad.jpeg 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-instagram-shopping-ad-480x277.jpeg 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/mobilemarketingmagazine.com\/instagram-shopping-creators\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Image source<\/em><\/a><\/p>\n<p><strong>\ud83c\udfac Action time: <\/strong>If you haven\u2019t tapped into Instagram yet for your ecommerce business, check out our <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2019\/08\/05\/instagram-ecommerce\">Instagram ecommerce guide<\/a> or our crash course on <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2018\/08\/07\/instagram-story-ads\">Instagram Story ads<\/a>.<\/p>\n<h3>Organic engagement<\/h3>\n<p>Not only does Instagram have the highest organic <strong>reach<\/strong> of all social media platforms (9.4%)&#8230;<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-linkedin-organic-reach.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - facebook, linkedin, instagram organic reach\" width=\"600\" height=\"503\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54119\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-linkedin-organic-reach.png 600w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-linkedin-organic-reach-480x402.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&#8230;but it also has the highest organic engagement<strong> rate, <\/strong>at <a href=\"https:\/\/www.socialinsider.io\/blog\/social-media-industry-benchmarks\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">1.16%<\/a> compared to 0.27% on Facebook and 0.07% on X.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-organic-engagement-rates.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - organic engagement rates\" width=\"720\" height=\"380\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54138\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-organic-engagement-rates.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-organic-engagement-rates-480x253.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p><strong>\ud83c\udfac Action time: <\/strong>To enhance your organic engagement on Instagram check out these <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/how-instagram-feed-works\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">9 ways to show up in the Instagram Feed<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/12\/01\/best-time-to-post-on-instagram\">find the right time to post on Instagram<\/a>.<\/p>\n<h3>Influencer marketing<\/h3>\n<p>This should come as no surprise, as many social media influencers use Instagram as their HQ. Marketers spend about <a href=\"https:\/\/www.emarketer.com\/chart\/226713\/influencer-marketing-channels-where-us-marketers-plan-spend-most-jan-2019-of-respondents\">69%<\/a> of their influencer budgets on Instagram, which is more than any other network (the second network on that list is YouTube at 11%).<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-influencer-marketing.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - influencer marketing channels\" width=\"600\" height=\"554\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54131\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-influencer-marketing.png 600w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-influencer-marketing-480x443.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p><strong>\ud83c\udfac Action time: <\/strong>To get started with influencer marketing, learn <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2018\/03\/21\/social-media-influencers\">how to find social media influencers in your industry <\/a>to help you <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2016\/08\/19\/influencer-marketing-content-promotion\">promote your content.<\/a><\/p>\n<h3>Tweets?<\/h3>\n<p>According to <a href=\"https:\/\/influencermarketinghub.com\/instagram-marketing-trends-2021\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Influencer Marketing Hub, <\/a>screenshots of tweets began growing in popularity on Instagram a year ago. This doesn&#8217;t mean you can take screenshots of your Tweets and expect them to succeed on Instagram. The trend is geared toward humorous tweets, so unless your tweets fit the bill, I&#8217;d suggest other <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2015\/02\/03\/repurposing-content\">content repurposing strategies<\/a>.<\/p>\n<h3>The most popular industries on Instagram<\/h3>\n<p>It also comes as no surprise that the <a href=\"https:\/\/blog.sellfy.com\/instagram-niches\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">industries that tend to thrive on Instagram<\/a> are: travel, beauty, fashion, health &amp; fitness, lifestyle, parenting, business, music, photography, food, animals.<\/p>\n<p>But here are some surprising finds from other studies. For one, the industries on Instagram with the highest reach rates were electronics, technology and software, and food and beverage.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-instagram-reach-rate.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - instagram reach rate\" width=\"720\" height=\"335\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54118\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-instagram-reach-rate.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-instagram-reach-rate-480x223.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bazaarvoice.com\/blog\/key-instagram-benchmarks-for-2021\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Image source<\/a><\/em><\/p>\n<p>And the same study found that the industries with the highest engagement rates on Instagram were technology, consumer goods, office supplies, and automotive.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-instagram-engagement-industries.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - instagram engagement rate by industry\" width=\"720\" height=\"364\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55312\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-instagram-engagement-industries.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-instagram-engagement-industries-480x243.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.rivaliq.com\/blog\/social-media-industry-benchmark-report\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">RivalIQ<\/a>, on the other hand, found that the top three industries for engagement were higher education, sports teams, and nonprofits (I excluded influencers here since, well, influencers).<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-instagram-engagement-by-industry.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - instagram engagement rate by industry\" width=\"650\" height=\"481\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55342\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-instagram-engagement-by-industry.png 650w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-instagram-engagement-by-industry-480x355.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 650px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>The data is a bit all over the place, so I think we can say that Instagram is good for a wide variety of industries. I mean, if office supplies can do it, anyone can.<\/p>\n<p><em>Psst&#8230;Have you been to the <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/local-marketing-lab\/local-social-media-marketing\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Social Media Marketing Lab?<\/a> <\/strong>It&#8217;s got tons of insider tips, best practices, and creative ideas for social media marketing.<\/em><a id=\"twitter\"><\/a><\/p>\n<div id=\"twitter-tidbits\"><\/div>\n<h2>Twitter\/X is the most popular social media platform for\u2026<\/h2>\n<p>Much more than just expressing your brand in 360 characters or less at a time. But that is, by far, its biggest distinguishing factor.<\/p>\n<h3>Customer service<\/h3>\n<p>The fast-paced, direct-connect nature of X has made it a go-to channel for customers to reach out to brands. In a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.businesswire.com\/news\/home\/20210126005014\/en\/Sprinklr-and-Twitter-Deliver-the-2021-Customer-Care-Report\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">recent survey<\/a>, two out of three people chose X as their preferred social media channel for customer care. And as a public-facing platform, brands that use it for customer service can also build their reputation at the same time.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-twitter-customer-service.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - twitter for customer engagement\" width=\"500\" height=\"712\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54130\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-twitter-customer-service.png 500w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-twitter-customer-service-480x684.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 500px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/blog.twitter.com\/en_gb\/a\/en-gb\/2016\/customer-service-on-twitter-and-the-impact-on-brands\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Image source<\/em><\/a><\/p>\n<h3>Images<\/h3>\n<p>According to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.quicksprout.com\/twitter-engagement\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Quicksprout<\/a>, videos may get favorited 49% more than images, but <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/social-media-image-sizes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">images<\/a> get 128% more retweets than videos. So if you want to expand your reach on X, I say go with the pics.<\/p>\n<h3>Advertising to males<\/h3>\n<p>While X\u2019s global user base is <a href=\"https:\/\/www.hootsuite.com\/resources\/digital2020-q4-update\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">70%<\/a> male and 30% female (male and female are the only gender options on X at this time), the gap is smaller in the U.S. (<a href=\"https:\/\/blog.hootsuite.com\/twitter-statistics\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">54%<\/a> male, 43% female).<\/p>\n<p>However, <a href=\"https:\/\/influencermarketinghub.com\/social-media-marketing-benchmark-report\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Influencer Marketing Hub<\/a> reports that X\u2019s <strong>advertisable audience is<\/strong> 60% male:<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-platforms-twitter-male.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - twitter male audience\" width=\"650\" height=\"333\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54121\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-platforms-twitter-male.png 650w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-platforms-twitter-male-480x246.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 650px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>But it is important to note that X has the smallest reach of all social media platforms in terms of advertising audience (6.5%, compared to Facebook at 36.7%).<\/p>\n<h3>News<\/h3>\n<p>So X is not the most popular social media platform people report on using for the news, according to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.pewresearch.org\/journalism\/2021\/01\/12\/news-use-across-social-media-platforms-in-2020\/\">Pew <\/a>(it\u2019s Facebook), but other sources beg to differ. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.statista.com\/statistics\/200843\/social-media-activities-by-platform-usa\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Statista<\/a> says 56% of X users get their news from X, compared to only 38% with Facebook.<\/p>\n<p>Another study shows that <a href=\"https:\/\/blog.hootsuite.com\/twitter-statistics\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">59%<\/a> of users use it regularly to get the news. Yet another source says that <a href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Social_media_as_a_news_source\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">74%<\/a> use it to get their news or headlines. And also, journalists make up <a href=\"https:\/\/www.oberlo.com\/blog\/twitter-statistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">almost 25% <\/a>of all verified accounts on X.<\/p>\n<p>I think but this comes down to what you consider news. Global news? Local news? News in your niche? News that wasn\u2019t supposed to be news? For example, we often first hear about news in the PPC world through #PPCchat on X.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/ppc-stories-barry-schwartz-google-ads-search-terms-report-tweet.png\" alt=\"tweet about search terms report bug 2021\" width=\"384\" height=\"440\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-52207\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/ppc-stories-barry-schwartz-google-ads-search-terms-report-tweet.png 384w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/ppc-stories-barry-schwartz-google-ads-search-terms-report-tweet-262x300.png 262w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 384px) 100vw, 384px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>This means that if your audience is on X, you may consider sharing industry news as a part of your strategy.<\/p>\n<p><strong>\ud83c\udfac Action time:<\/strong> Get up to speed on the <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/twitter-updates-2021\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">latest X features for marketing<\/a> and use them to engage your audience.<\/p>\n<h3>Young, educated, wealthy city dwellers and Democrats<\/h3>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.pewresearch.org\/fact-tank\/2019\/08\/02\/10-facts-about-americans-and-twitter\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Pew<\/a> tells us that X users are younger, more highly educated, and wealthier than the general public. 42% of U.S. adults on X have a least a college degree, versus 31% of all Americans, and 41% of all adult X users earn at least $75,000 a year versus 32% of all American adults.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/twitter-demographics.png\" alt=\"twitter demographics\" width=\"420\" height=\"494\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55403\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/twitter-demographics.png 420w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/twitter-demographics-255x300.png 255w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Sources also show that most X users in the U.S. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.pewresearch.org\/fact-tank\/2019\/04\/10\/share-of-u-s-adults-using-social-media-including-facebook-is-mostly-unchanged-since-2018\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">live in cities<\/a>, and that <a href=\"https:\/\/www.pewresearch.org\/journalism\/2021\/01\/12\/news-use-across-social-media-platforms-in-2020\/pj_2021-01-12_news-social-media_0-04\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">65%<\/a> of users are Democrats, vs 33% Republicans. You can see a similar disparity on Instagram and LinkedIn.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-twitter-democrats.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - by democrat vs republican\" width=\"720\" height=\"125\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54129\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-twitter-democrats.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-twitter-democrats-480x83.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>The most popular industries on X<\/h3>\n<p>As with any platform in this post, most businesses can find a way to benefit from X marketing\u2014it\u2019s about how effectively you use it. But there are some categories that seem to have more ease with success than others.<\/p>\n<p>According to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.rivaliq.com\/blog\/social-media-industry-benchmark-report\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Rival IQ<\/a>, verticals with the highest engagement rates on X are education, sports teams, food and beverage, alcohol, and nonprofits.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-twitter-engagement.png\" alt=\"most popular industries on twitter\" width=\"600\" height=\"625\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54120\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-twitter-engagement.png 600w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-twitter-engagement-480x500.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw\" \/><a href=\"https:\/\/influencermarketinghub.com\/social-media-marketing-benchmark-report\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em><\/em><\/a><\/p>\n<p>According to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.socialinsider.io\/blog\/social-media-industry-benchmarks\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Social Insider<\/a>, the industries that get the most engagement on X are restaurants, auto, and healthcare businesses. Another <a href=\"https:\/\/enlyft.com\/tech\/products\/twitter-analytics\">study<\/a> showed that automotive, computer software, and retail industries are the biggest users of X analytics. It&#8217;s also worth noting that X is a top channel for <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\/pmc\/articles\/PMC6025547\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">healthcare communication<\/a>.<\/p>\n<div id=\"linkedin-low-down\"><\/div>\n<h2>LinkedIn is the most popular social media platform for\u2026<\/h2>\n<p>Do I even need to say it? But actually, there\u2019s more to LinkedIn than you might think. Let\u2019s learn about some of its strong points.<\/p>\n<h3>B2B marketing<\/h3>\n<p>As a professional, business-based social media network, I should hope that LinkedIn is the best for B2B marketing. After some fact-checking, we can safely conclude that it is.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Linkedin makes up over <a href=\"https:\/\/www.omnicoreagency.com\/linkedin-statistics\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">half<\/a> of all social traffic to b2b websites and blogs.<\/li>\n<li>There are 61 million senior-level influencers and <a href=\"https:\/\/business.linkedin.com\/marketing-solutions\/blog\/linkedin-company-pages\/2020\/reaching-your-audience-on-linkedin-with-precision--a-primer--inf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">65 million decision-makers on LinkedIn<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/business.linkedin.com\/content\/dam\/me\/business\/en-us\/marketing-solutions\/resources\/pdfs\/tactical-plan-ebook-2019.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">80% of B2B leads<\/a> come from LinkedIn.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Also, according to Sprout Social <a href=\"https:\/\/sproutsocial.com\/insights\/new-social-media-demographics\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">70%<\/a> of LinkedIn users live outside the US, making it a solid platform for international B2B businesses.<\/p>\n<p><strong>\ud83c\udfac Action time: <\/strong>Check to make sure you&#8217;re using all of the<a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/08\/19\/linkedin-company-page-features-examples\"> LinkedIn company page features<\/a> available to you for maximum engagement<\/p>\n<h3>Organic engagement<\/h3>\n<p>It\u2019s no Instagram, but LinkedIn\u2019s organic engagement rate is double that of Facebook, which makes sense. People use this platform specifically for business and networking purposes, so they are naturally receptive to posts and messages of transactional or marketing nature.<\/p>\n<p>Also, with fewer posts per day and members than Facebook, the competition is lower. So it\u2019s no wonder why <a href=\"https:\/\/sproutsocial.com\/insights\/instagram-stats\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\u200b95%<\/a> of B2B content marketers use LinkedIn as an organic marketing channel.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-linkedin-organic.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - organic B2B social media platforms\" width=\"600\" height=\"622\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54114\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-linkedin-organic.png 600w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-linkedin-organic-480x498.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p><strong>\ud83c\udfac Action time: <\/strong>Follow these <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2020\/06\/24\/b2b-social-media-tips\">nine B2B social media tips<\/a> and get familiar with our <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2019\/03\/05\/linkedin-advertising\">LinkedIn advertising cheat sheet.<\/a><\/p>\n<h3>Long-form content<\/h3>\n<p>360 characters or less may be ideal for X, but an analysis by <a href=\"https:\/\/okdork.com\/linkedin-publishing-success\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Okdork<\/a> found that long-form content (the &#8220;article&#8221; post type, between 1,900-2,000 words) gets the greatest number of views, likes, comments, and shares on LinkedIn.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-linkedin-word-count.jpeg\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - linkedin post performance by word count\" width=\"600\" height=\"493\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54128\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-linkedin-word-count.jpeg 600w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-linkedin-word-count-480x394.jpeg 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p><strong>\ud83c\udfac Action time: <\/strong>To write an article, simply navigate to the &#8220;Start a post&#8221; box at the top of your <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/08\/19\/linkedin-company-page-features-examples\">company page<\/a> and choose &#8220;write article.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-linkedin-articles.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - linkedin article type\" width=\"600\" height=\"193\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55308\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-linkedin-articles.png 600w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-linkedin-articles-480x154.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>Kumbaya and inspiration<\/h3>\n<p>Don&#8217;t let the whole B2B thing on LinkedIn fool you\u2014this platform has a warm and fuzzy side too. Members don&#8217;t just use LinkedIn to find jobs and network, but also to better themselves, personally and professionally. As such, <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/inspirational-quotes-for-small-business-owners\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">inspiring<\/a> and community-building content about leadership and core values has a nice home here, whether you&#8217;re celebrating others or expressing your own.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-linkedin-community.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - linkedin post example\" width=\"400\" height=\"659\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54135\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-linkedin-community.png 400w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-linkedin-community-182x300.png 182w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Instagram isn&#8217;t the only place for rainbows and unicorns.<\/em><\/p>\n<p><strong>\ud83c\udfac Action time: <\/strong>Take a look at this list of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/06\/09\/company-core-values\">over 200 core values<\/a> and nail down yours. Then make this a common theme in your posts for both your company page or your personal page.<\/p>\n<h3>Privacy<\/h3>\n<p>When asked which social media platforms they feel most confident in about protecting their privacy and data, consumers ranked LinkedIn first, and Instagram, X, TikTok, and Facebook last. So for what it&#8217;s worth, your LinkedIn audience data might be your most reliable.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-by-security.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - by privacy\" width=\"236\" height=\"549\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54139\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-by-security.png 236w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-by-security-129x300.png 129w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 236px) 100vw, 236px\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.emarketer.com\/content\/facebook-ranks-last-in-digital-trust-among-users\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Image source<\/em><\/a><\/p>\n<p><strong>\ud83c\udfac Action time: <\/strong>Learn how to use <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2020\/09\/02\/linkedin-website-demographics\">LinkedIn Website Demographics<\/a> to perfect your B2B buyer personas and supercharge your ad performance.<\/p>\n<h3>The most popular industries on LinkedIn<\/h3>\n<p>The <a href=\"https:\/\/blog.linkboost.co\/linkedin-industries-full-list-analysis-and-rankings-2019-2021\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">most popular categories on LinkedIn<\/a> are IT, hospital and health, construction, retail, and education management. IT, in particular, makes up 4% of all profiles on LinkedIn.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-top-industries-linkedin.png\" alt=\"most popular industries on linkedin\" width=\"600\" height=\"343\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-54141\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-top-industries-linkedin.png 600w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-top-industries-linkedin-480x274.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>As for advertising, the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.theb2bhouse.com\/linkedin-ad-benchmarks\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">B2B House<\/a> says that public administration, retail, and manufacturing get the most engagement.<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Public administration<\/li>\n<li>Retail<\/li>\n<li>Manufacturing<\/li>\n<li>Consumer goods<\/li>\n<li>Education<\/li>\n<li>Transportation &amp; logistics<\/li>\n<li>Finance<\/li>\n<li>Corporate services<\/li>\n<li>Media &amp; communications<\/li>\n<li>Healthcare<\/li>\n<li>Hardware &amp; networking<\/li>\n<li>Software &amp; IT<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-engagement-rates-linkedin.png\" alt=\"most popular social media platforms - lInkedin ad engagement rates by industry\" width=\"642\" height=\"450\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55315\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/most-popular-social-media-platforms-e